d results, with new tensions emerging across social groups. Becoming Rwandan argues that although the Rwandan government utilizes global discourses in national policy documents, the way in which teachers and students engage with these global models distorts the intention of the government, resulting in unintended consequences and undermining a sustainable peace.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aCitizenshipzRwanda. 0aEducation and statezRwanda. 0aEducationxSocial aspectszRwanda. 0aGenocidezRwandaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPeace-buildingzRwanda. 0aReconciliation. 0aTransitional justicezRwanda. 70(DE-588)10691267480(DE-627)8213520160(DE-576)428419232aTransitional Justice2gnd 70(DE-588)4006566-20(DE-627)1063769850(DE-576)208866248aBilanz2gnd 70(DE-588)4006650-20(DE-627)1063768100(DE-576)208866450aBildung2gnd 70(DE-588)4006667-80(DE-627)1063767720(DE-576)208866531aBildungspolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4015482-80(DE-627)1063365920(DE-576)208911901aErziehung2gnd 70(DE-588)4018522-90(DE-627)1063254420(DE-576)208924884aFriedenserziehung2gnd 70(DE-588)4032081-90(DE-627)1062629710(DE-576)208995544aKonflikt2gnd 70(DE-588)4041279-90(DE-627)1062198390(DE-576)209044276aNation2gnd 70(DE-588)4063213-10(DE-627)1045523870(DE-576)209147822aVersöhnung2gnd 70(DE-588)4112646-40(DE-627)1058356840(DE-576)209469684aAuswirkung2gnd 70(DE-588)4385295-60(DE-627)1882386460(DE-576)211887714aErgebnis2gnd 70(DE-588)7604836-60(DE-627)5602287400(DE-576)278419313aFriedenskonsolidierung2gnd 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh  aRwanda, Rwandan, genocide, political violence, human rights, education, post-genocide, government, Rwandan government, peace, unification, patriotism, citizenship, reconciliation, teachers, students, global models, school, peacebuilding, state-building,